<!-- Q31 -->
<div class="problem" id="q31">
  <div class="problem-header">
    <span class="pnum">31</span>
    <span class="answer-badge">Answer: D</span>
    <span class="topic-tag">Comparison Test / Squeeze Theorem for Series</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <p>Given \(0 < a_n < \dfrac{2n}{n+1}\), which statement must be true?</p>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Analyze the bound</div>
      <p>\(\dfrac{2n}{n+1}\to 2\neq 0\), so the bounding series \(\sum\dfrac{2n}{n+1}\) <strong>diverges</strong> (terms \(\not\to 0\)).</p>
      <p>Since \(a_n\) is bounded above by a divergent sequence's terms — but this tells us nothing definitive about \(\sum a_n\). The comparison test requires a bound by a convergent series to conclude convergence.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="key-insight">Answer: <strong>(D)</strong> \(\sum\dfrac{2n}{n+1}\) diverges, but \(\sum a_n\) may or may not converge.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="return-link"><a href="#answer-key-b">↑ Return to answer key</a></div>
</div>

<!-- Q32 -->
<div class="problem" id="q32">
  <div class="problem-header">
    <span class="pnum">32</span>
    <span class="answer-badge">Answer: C</span>
    <span class="topic-tag">Accumulation / Rate Problem</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <p>Sand is poured at rate \(r(t)=\dfrac{25t}{t+1}\) ft³/min. Initial amount: 100 ft³. Amount after 30 minutes?</p>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Integrate the rate</div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[\int_0^{30}\frac{25t}{t+1}\,dt = 25\int_0^{30}\left(1-\frac{1}{t+1}\right)dt = 25\left[t-\ln(t+1)\right]_0^{30}\]
      </div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[= 25\left(30-\ln 31\right) \approx 25(30-3.434) \approx 25(26.566)\approx 664.1\]
      </div>
      <p>Total: \(100+664\approx 764\).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="key-insight">Answer: <strong>(C) 764</strong>.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="return-link"><a href="#answer-key-b">↑ Return to answer key</a></div>
</div>

