<!-- Q36 -->
<div class="problem" id="q36">
  <div class="problem-header">
    <span class="pnum">36</span>
    <span class="answer-badge">Answer: C</span>
    <span class="topic-tag">Integration by Parts with Table / FTC</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <p>Given \(G(x)=\displaystyle\int_0^x g(t)\,dt\), find \(\displaystyle\int_1^3 x^2 g''(x)\,dx\) using the table below.</p>
    <table style="border-collapse:collapse; margin: 12px 0 16px; font-size:0.95rem;">
      <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--rule);">
        <th style="padding:6px 20px; text-align:center; color:var(--muted);">x</th>
        <th style="padding:6px 20px; text-align:center; color:var(--muted);">1</th>
        <th style="padding:6px 20px; text-align:center; color:var(--muted);">3</th>
      </tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">\(G(x)\)</td><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">3</td><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">4</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">\(G'(x)\)</td><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">6</td><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">2</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">\(G''(x)\)</td><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">5</td><td style="padding:5px 20px; text-align:center;">1</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p>Since \(G(x)=\int_0^x g(t)\,dt\), we have \(G'(x)=g(x)\) and \(G''(x)=g'(x)\). So the table gives us: \(g(1)=6,\; g(3)=2,\; g'(1)=5,\; g'(3)=1,\; G(1)=3,\; G(3)=4\).</p>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Integration by parts — first application</div>
      <p>Let \(u=x^2,\; dv=g''(x)\,dx\), so \(du=2x\,dx,\; v=g'(x)\):</p>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[\int_1^3 x^2g''(x)\,dx = \Big[x^2g'(x)\Big]_1^3-\int_1^3 2x\,g'(x)\,dx\]
      </div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[= \big(9\cdot g'(3)-1\cdot g'(1)\big) - \int_1^3 2x\,g'(x)\,dx = (9\cdot1-1\cdot5)-\int_1^3 2x\,g'(x)\,dx = 4-\int_1^3 2x\,g'(x)\,dx\]
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Integration by parts — second application</div>
      <p>For \(\int_1^3 2x\,g'(x)\,dx\): let \(u=2x,\; dv=g'(x)\,dx\), so \(du=2\,dx,\; v=g(x)\):</p>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[\int_1^3 2x\,g'(x)\,dx = \Big[2x\,g(x)\Big]_1^3 - \int_1^3 2g(x)\,dx\]
      </div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[= (6\cdot g(3)-2\cdot g(1)) - 2\int_1^3 g(x)\,dx = (6\cdot2-2\cdot6) - 2\int_1^3 g(x)\,dx = 0 - 2\int_1^3 g(x)\,dx\]
      </div>
      <p>Since \(G'(x)=g(x)\), we have \(\displaystyle\int_1^3 g(x)\,dx = G(3)-G(1)=4-3=1\).</p>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[\int_1^3 2x\,g'(x)\,dx = 0-2(1) = -2\]
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Combine</div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[\int_1^3 x^2g''(x)\,dx = 4-(-2) = 6\]
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="key-insight">Answer: <strong>(C) 6</strong>.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="return-link"><a href="#answer-key-b">↑ Return to answer key</a></div>
</div>

