    <span class="answer-badge">Answer: C</span>
    <span class="topic-tag">Volume of Revolution (Calculator)</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <p>Revolve \(y=\sqrt{x}+\dfrac{3\cos x}{x}\) about the \(x\)-axis from \(x=\pi/2\) to \(x=3\pi\). Find the volume.</p>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Disk/Washer method</div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[V=\pi\int_{\pi/2}^{3\pi}\left(\sqrt{x}+\frac{3\cos x}{x}\right)^2dx\]
      </div>
      <p>Using a graphing calculator: \(V\approx 129.183\).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="key-insight">Answer: <strong>(C) 129.183</strong>.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="return-link"><a href="#answer-key-b">↑ Return to answer key</a></div>
</div>

<!-- Q40 -->
<div class="problem" id="q40">
  <div class="problem-header">
    <span class="pnum">40</span>
    <span class="answer-badge">Answer: C</span>
    <span class="topic-tag">Parametric Speed</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <p>Given \(x(t)=t^2+3t,\;y(t)=2t^3-21t^2+60t\), find the speed at \(t=3\).</p>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Compute derivatives at t = 3</div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[x'(t)=2t+3 \implies x'(3)=6+3=9\]
      </div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[y'(t)=6t^2-42t+60 \implies y'(3)=54-126+60=-12\]
      </div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[\text{Speed}=\sqrt{9^2+(-12)^2}=\sqrt{81+144}=\sqrt{225}=15\]
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="key-insight">Answer: <strong>(C) 15</strong>.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="return-link"><a href="#answer-key-b">↑ Return to answer key</a></div>
</div>

<!-- Q41 -->
<div class="problem" id="q41">
  <div class="problem-header">
    <span class="pnum">41</span>
    <span class="answer-badge">Answer: A</span>
    <span class="topic-tag">Taylor Polynomial Approximation of an Integral</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <p>Use the second-degree Taylor polynomial for \(G(x)=\displaystyle\int_0^x g(t)\,dt\) about \(x=1\) to approximate \(\displaystyle\int_0^{0.8}g(t)\,dt\).</p>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Build the Taylor polynomial for G</div>
      <p>From the table: \(G(1)=3,\;G'(1)=g(1)=6,\;G''(1)=g'(1)=5\).</p>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[G(x)\approx 3+6(x-1)+\frac{5}{2}(x-1)^2\]
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Evaluate at x = 0.8</div>
      <p>Since \(G(0)=\displaystyle\int_0^0 g(t)\,dt=0\), we have \(\displaystyle\int_0^{0.8}g(t)\,dt = G(0.8)-G(0)=G(0.8)\).</p>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[G(0.8)\approx 3+6(0.8-1)+\frac{5}{2}(0.8-1)^2 = 3+6(-0.2)+\frac{5}{2}(0.04) = 3-1.2+0.1 = 1.9\]
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="key-insight">Answer: <strong>(A) 1.9</strong>.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="return-link"><a href="#answer-key-b">↑ Return to answer key</a></div>
</div>

