<!-- Q44 -->
<div class="problem" id="q44">
  <div class="problem-header">
    <span class="pnum">44</span>
    <span class="answer-badge">Answer: C</span>
    <span class="topic-tag">Related Rates — Cone</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <p>Sand on a conical pile at 25 ft³/min. Radius = half of height. Find \(dr/dt\) when \(h=10\) ft.</p>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Express volume in terms of r alone</div>
      <p>Since \(r=h/2\), we have \(h=2r\). \(V=\tfrac{1}{3}\pi r^2 h=\tfrac{1}{3}\pi r^2(2r)=\tfrac{2\pi}{3}r^3\).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Differentiate</div>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[\frac{dV}{dt}=2\pi r^2\frac{dr}{dt}\]
      </div>
      <p>When \(h=10\Rightarrow r=5\):</p>
      <div class="math-display">
        \[25=2\pi(25)\frac{dr}{dt}\implies \frac{dr}{dt}=\frac{25}{50\pi}=\frac{1}{2\pi}\approx 0.159\]
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="key-insight">Answer: <strong>(C) 0.159</strong>.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="return-link"><a href="#answer-key-b">↑ Return to answer key</a></div>
</div>

<!-- Q45 -->
<div class="problem" id="q45">
  <div class="problem-header">
    <span class="pnum">45</span>
    <span class="answer-badge">Answer: D</span>
    <span class="topic-tag">Extreme Value Theorem</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <p>\(f\) continuous on \([1,3]\), \(f(1)=-2\), \(f(3)=4\). What does EVT guarantee?</p>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Recall EVT</div>
      <p>The Extreme Value Theorem guarantees that a continuous function on a closed interval attains its absolute maximum and minimum values on that interval.</p>
      <p>Since \(f(1)=-2\) and \(f(3)=4\), and \(f\) is continuous, \(f\) attains an absolute max \(\geq 4\) and an absolute min \(\leq -2\). The EVT guarantees the function attains these extremes — specifically that the absolute max value \(f(c)\geq f(3)=4\) for all \(x\in[1,3]\).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="key-insight">Answer: <strong>(D)</strong> \(f\) attains an absolute maximum value \(f(c)\geq f(x)\) for all \(x\in[1,3]\).</div>
  </div>
  <div class="return-link"><a href="#answer-key-b">↑ Return to answer key</a></div>
</div>

